parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion and Failure of Control Arms
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of control arms can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: and difficulty steering; control arms may break or fracture
causing the vehicle to become unstable or inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the frame can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Corrosion and rust on the frame
and difficulty steering; the frame may break or fracture
causing the vehicle to become unstable or inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of suspension and steering components can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: and difficulty steering; the vehicle may pull to one side or vibrate excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light remains illuminated on the dashboard
the airbag system fails to deploy in an accident
the airbag sensor light comes on
and the vehicle's airbag system is rendered non-functional.
